race.description: Marty Nelson Refrigeration Electrical & AC Handicap
race.comment: BOUNDING BON (4) took nine attempts but finally grabbed a well-deserved breakthrough win nine days ago, leading all the way and easily accounting for his rivals in a 1200m Parkes maiden. Not a great deal of depth to the form here so a follow-up win is on the cards. PICKAXE (1) missed the start then got going late for a midfield finish when resuming over this distance at Gunnedah a fortnight ago. Placed two from three when second-up. Hasn't won in ages but this sets up nicely. The consistent WING NUT (6) made late inroads to finish third in a Class 3 over a slightly longer journey at Cowra recently. Down in grade and appeals as a sound each-way prospect. SPRING PROSPECT (7) ran a very cheeky race in front when fresh from a spell over 1200m at Canterbury last time out. Lightly raced mare who should give backers a sight again. DIVINE SINNER (5) isn't the most reliable conveyance but has the ability to fill a top four spot.
